```
@serve.deployment(ray_actor_options={"num_gpus": 2})
def func(*args):
    return do_something_with_my_gpus()
```
This will allocate 2 GPUs for each replica of the deployment. You can also specify a fractional number of GPUs to pack multiple replicas together on a machine with fewer GPUs than replicas.

Alternatively, you can use the `resources_per_trial` parameter in the `tune.run` function to specify the number of GPUs for each trial in a Tune experiment. For example:
```
resources_per_trial = {"cpu": 1, "gpu": 2}
tune.run(train_fn, resources_per_trial=resources_per_trial)
```
This will allocate 2 GPUs for each trial in the experiment.

